# Component Patterns

> For comprehensive snippets and layout reference, read `src/tools/CLAUDE.md`.
> This file is the enforced checklist derived from the full code review.

---

## Error extraction — always use the utility

Use `extractErrorMessage` from `src/lib/extractErrorMessage.ts` in all `catch` blocks.
Never inline the verbose `e instanceof Error ? e.message : String(e ?? "...")` pattern.

```ts
import { extractErrorMessage } from "../../lib/extractErrorMessage";

try { ... }
catch (e) {
  setError(extractErrorMessage(e, "Operation failed"));
}
```

---

## Draft persistence — required for all non-sensitive text-input tools

Every tool with a user-typed text field must persist the draft across reloads:

```ts
const { setDraft } = useDraftInput(TOOL_ID);
const [input, setInput] = useState("");
useRestoreStringDraft(TOOL_ID, setInput);
```

Call `setDraft(value)` in the `onChange` handler alongside `setInput(value)`.

**Exceptions (no draft hooks):**
- Sensitive tools (JWT, AES, TOTP, Password, Basic Auth) — see bridge-history-privacy.mdc
- Pure generators with no free-text field (only selects/checkboxes/sliders)

If a generator has even one user-typed field (e.g. a custom alphabet input), that
field must be persisted. "Pure generator" only applies when there is literally no
field the user types into.

