## Clear buttons — always call handleClear()

✕ buttons and "Clear" links must always call the tool's `handleClear()` function.
Never use an inline partial reset — inline resets leave `output` stale, so old
results stay visible after the input is gone.

```tsx
// ✅ Correct
const handleClear = useCallback(() => {
  setInput("");
  setDraft("");
  setOutput(null);
  setFileName(null);
  setError(null);
}, [setDraft]);

<button onClick={handleClear}>✕</button>

// ❌ Wrong — output not cleared, stale results remain
<button onClick={() => { setFileName(null); setInput(""); }}>✕</button>
```

