## File upload — always handle reader.onerror

Every `FileReader` usage must have an `onerror` handler. Without it, failures
(locked file, unreadable binary) are silently swallowed.

```tsx
const reader = new FileReader();
reader.onload = (ev) => {
  const text = ev.target?.result as string;
  setInputValue(text);
  setDraft(text);
};
reader.onerror = () => {
  setFileDropError("Failed to read file — it may be locked or unreadable.");
};
reader.readAsText(file);
e.target.value = "";
```

